{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}]}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"property","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"overlayBounds","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}],"title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","title":"MapLibre","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"overlayBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}]}}}